---
import BaseLayout from '../layouts/BaseLayout.astro';

const base = import.meta.env.BASE_URL;
const jobs = [
  {
    question: 'What changed when the requests started failing?',
    answer: 'Search retained container logs and compare the first bad request with Docker health, restart, OOM, and resource events from the same window.',
  },
  {
    question: 'Is the .NET runtime under pressure?',
    answer: 'Watch or record CPU, allocation, GC, ThreadPool, contention, and memory counters without attaching an interactive shell to the workload.',
  },
  {
    question: 'What evidence will we need after the incident?',
    answer: 'Capture a bounded stack snapshot, EventPipe trace, or dump and keep it with the logs, notes, and exact time range that explain why it was taken.',
  },
] as const;
---

<BaseLayout
  title="Tracebag — self-hosted debugging for .NET containers"
  description="Search logs, inspect .NET runtime pressure, and preserve diagnostic evidence from Dockerized .NET applications."
>
  <section class="hero shell">
    <div class="hero-copy">
      <h1>Debug a .NET container after the easy checks stop helping.</h1>
      <p class="lead">Tracebag keeps its logs, runtime counters, Docker state, stack snapshots, and traces in one incident timeline. It runs on your Docker host and stores the evidence there.</p>
      <div class="actions">
        <a class="button" href={`${base}getting-started/`}>Install Tracebag</a>
        <a class="button button-secondary" href={`${base}demo/`}>See the demo investigation</a>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <section class="product-proof shell" aria-labelledby="capture-caption">
    <figure>
      <div class="screenshot-scroll" tabindex="0" aria-label="Scrollable Tracebag incident screenshot">
        <img src={`${base}screenshots/demo-contention-overview.jpg`} alt="Tracebag incident with an ordered capture timeline and its evidence" width="1265" height="712" loading="eager" />
      </div>
      <div class="screenshot-scroll-meta">
        <span>Swipe to inspect</span>
        <a href={`${base}screenshots/demo-contention-overview.jpg`}>Open full size <span aria-hidden="true">↗</span></a>
      </div>
      <figcaption id="capture-caption">
        <strong>A real capture from the included lock-contention demo.</strong>
        <span>The ordered timeline is on the left; the logs, counter window, Docker state, and diagnostic artifacts are kept beside it.</span>
      </figcaption>
    </figure>
  </section>

  <section class="section shell" id="features">
    <div class="section-heading plain-heading">
      <h2>Start with the question you actually have.</h2>
      <p>Tracebag is not another general-purpose dashboard. It is a place to investigate one difficult failure and retain enough evidence to explain it later.</p>
    </div>
    <div class="job-list">
      {jobs.map((job, index) => (
        <article>
          <span class="job-number">{String(index + 1).padStart(2, '0')}</span>
          <h3>{job.question}</h3>
          <p>{job.answer}</p>
        </article>
      ))}
    </div>
  </section>

  <section class="section section-muted investigation">
    <div class="shell investigation-grid">
      <div class="investigation-copy">
        <h2>An endpoint stalls. Requests queue. CPU alone does not explain it.</h2>
        <p>The demo API can reproduce that exact situation with a bounded lock-contention workload. Tracebag records the counter window, captures stacks and a threading trace, and links the useful findings back to the original evidence.</p>
        <p>Nothing in the demo is a mock screenshot or a scripted result. It runs the same images and diagnostic runners used for another opted-in .NET container.</p>
        <a class="text-link" href={`${base}demo/`}>Follow the ten-minute investigation <span aria-hidden="true">→</span></a>
      </div>
      <figure>
        <div class="screenshot-scroll" tabindex="0" aria-label="Scrollable Tracebag correlation screenshot">
          <img src={`${base}screenshots/demo-contention-correlation.jpg`} alt="Tracebag correlation view aligning runtime pressure, trace events, and logs" width="1265" height="712" loading="lazy" />
        </div>
        <div class="screenshot-scroll-meta">
          <span>Swipe to inspect</span>
          <a href={`${base}screenshots/demo-contention-correlation.jpg`}>Open full size <span aria-hidden="true">↗</span></a>
        </div>
        <figcaption>Runtime pressure, trace events, and logs aligned around the same incident window.</figcaption>
      </figure>
    </div>
  </section>

  <section class="section shell boundary-section">
    <div class="boundary-intro">
      <h2>It needs the Docker socket. That is a serious permission.</h2>
      <p>Tracebag uses Docker access to inspect opted-in workloads and launch temporary diagnostic runners. It should run only on a host you control, bound to localhost or protected by a trusted HTTPS proxy.</p>
      <a class="text-link" href={`${base}security/`}>Read the complete security model <span aria-hidden="true">→</span></a>
    </div>
    <div class="boundary-details">
      <h3>The default boundaries</h3>
      <ul>
        <li>Containers remain invisible until they carry the opt-in label.</li>
        <li>The browser cannot submit shell commands or arbitrary Docker requests.</li>
        <li>Diagnostics use fixed profiles, hard limits, and network-isolated runners.</li>
        <li>Authentication is enabled and the service binds to localhost.</li>
        <li>Evidence stays local unless an operator explicitly exports it.</li>
      </ul>
    </div>
  </section>

  <section class="section demo-cta">
    <div class="shell demo-cta-inner">
      <div>
        <h2>Try it on an API designed to fail safely.</h2>
        <p>Generate CPU pressure, allocations, contention, slow requests, downstream failures, or ThreadPool starvation, then investigate the result in Tracebag.</p>
      </div>
      <div class="actions">
        <a class="button" href={`${base}getting-started/`}>Install with Docker</a>
        <a class="button button-secondary" href="https://github.com/poodlelab/tracebag">Browse the source</a>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>
</BaseLayout>

<style>
  .hero { padding-block: clamp(5rem, 10vw, 8rem) clamp(3.5rem, 7vw, 5.5rem); }
  .hero-copy { max-width: 880px; }
  .hero h1 { font-size: clamp(3rem, 7.2vw, 6rem); max-width: 980px; }
  .hero .lead { max-width: 770px; }

  .product-proof { padding-bottom: clamp(5rem, 9vw, 8rem); }
  figure { margin: 0; }
  .product-proof figure { border-block: 1px solid var(--border-strong); padding-block: 0.9rem 1rem; }
  .product-proof .screenshot-scroll { border: 1px solid var(--border); }
  .product-proof figcaption { align-items: baseline; display: grid; gap: 0.6rem 2rem; grid-template-columns: minmax(16rem, 0.8fr) 1.2fr; padding-top: 1rem; }
  .product-proof figcaption strong { font-size: 0.92rem; }
  .product-proof figcaption span { color: var(--muted); font-size: 0.86rem; line-height: 1.55; }

  .plain-heading { max-width: 760px; }
  .plain-heading h2 { margin-bottom: 1.2rem; }
  .job-list { border-top: 1px solid var(--border-strong); }
  .job-list article { align-items: start; border-bottom: 1px solid var(--border); display: grid; gap: 1.5rem; grid-template-columns: 3rem minmax(15rem, 0.8fr) 1.2fr; padding-block: 1.7rem; }
  .job-number { color: var(--accent); font: 0.72rem var(--mono); padding-top: 0.25rem; }
  .job-list h3 { font-size: 1.08rem; line-height: 1.35; margin: 0; }
  .job-list p { color: var(--muted-bright); font-size: 0.93rem; line-height: 1.65; margin: 0; }

  .investigation-grid { align-items: center; display: grid; gap: clamp(3rem, 7vw, 6rem); grid-template-columns: 0.75fr 1.25fr; }
  .investigation-grid > * { min-width: 0; }
  .investigation-copy { width: 100%; }
  .investigation-copy h2 { font-size: clamp(2.1rem, 4vw, 3.4rem); }
  .investigation-copy p { color: var(--muted-bright); line-height: 1.75; }
  .investigation figure { border: 1px solid var(--border); min-width: 0; width: 100%; }
  .investigation figcaption { color: var(--muted); font-size: 0.8rem; line-height: 1.5; padding: 0.8rem 1rem; }

  .boundary-section { align-items: start; display: grid; gap: clamp(3rem, 8vw, 7rem); grid-template-columns: 1fr 1fr; }
  .boundary-intro p { color: var(--muted-bright); line-height: 1.75; }
  .boundary-details { border-top: 1px solid var(--border-strong); padding-top: 1.4rem; }
  .boundary-details h3 { font-size: 0.95rem; margin-bottom: 1.2rem; }
  .boundary-details ul { color: var(--muted-bright); display: grid; gap: 0.9rem; list-style: none; margin: 0; padding: 0; }
  .boundary-details li { border-bottom: 1px solid var(--border); line-height: 1.55; padding: 0 0 0.9rem 1.4rem; position: relative; }
  .boundary-details li::before { color: var(--accent); content: '—'; left: 0; position: absolute; }

  .text-link { color: var(--text); display: inline-block; font-weight: 700; margin-top: 1rem; text-decoration: none; }
  .text-link span { color: var(--accent); margin-left: 0.35rem; }
  .demo-cta { border-top: 1px solid var(--border); }
  .demo-cta-inner { align-items: end; display: grid; gap: 3rem; grid-template-columns: 1fr auto; }
  .demo-cta h2 { font-size: clamp(2.2rem, 4.5vw, 3.8rem); margin-bottom: 1rem; max-width: 760px; }
  .demo-cta p { color: var(--muted-bright); line-height: 1.7; margin: 0; max-width: 720px; }
  .demo-cta .actions { justify-content: end; margin: 0; }

  @media (max-width: 850px) {
    .investigation-grid, .boundary-section, .demo-cta-inner { grid-template-columns: 1fr; }
    .investigation-copy { max-width: 680px; }
    .demo-cta .actions { justify-content: start; }
  }

  @media (max-width: 700px) {
    .hero { padding-top: 4rem; }
    .hero h1 { letter-spacing: -0.05em; }
    .product-proof figcaption, .job-list article { grid-template-columns: 1fr; }
    .job-list article { gap: 0.7rem; }
    .job-number { padding: 0; }
    .product-proof figcaption { gap: 0.4rem; }
  }
</style>
